{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-post-js","path":"/simple-living/","webpackCompilationHash":"adc5a099dfbc8e80d26d","result":{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"Jeremy Abroad","author":"Jeremy Bernier"}},"markdownRemark":{"id":"280ea787-859d-5556-b739-aa661a3e97ab","excerpt":"Here are the material possessions that I need to live a life that I’m content with:ShelterFoodLaptop with internet connectionCell phone with…","html":"<p>Here are the material possessions that I need to live a life that I’m content with:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Shelter</li>\n<li>Food</li>\n<li>Laptop with internet connection</li>\n<li>Cell phone with internet connection</li>\n</ul>\n<p>That’s it.</p>\n<p>Anything else is pure luxury.</p>\n<p>It feels like the media constantly shoves products down our throats, making us feel like we need to buy this crap we don’t need to feel complete.</p>\n<p><img src=\"./1-UNCLE+SAM+-+CONSUME+-+THEY+LIVE+-+HAL+HEFNER.jpg\" alt=\"CONSUME\"></p>\n<p>But fulfillment via material possessions is at best temporary - your new car makes you happy for a week, and then you get used to it and that “hole” in your life is still there.</p>\n<p>The only way to truly feel fulfilled is to get rid of this hole, to rid yourself of any dependency on external material possessions for your own internal happiness. </p>\n<p>Most material purchases are for status signaling anyways (eg. expensive house/car, luxury handbag). I think it’s pretty self-explanatory that buying something just to impress other (shallow) people is absolutely pathetic.</p>\n\n          <div\n            class=\"gatsby-resp-iframe-wrapper\"\n            style=\"padding-bottom: 56.25%; position: relative; height: 0; overflow: hidden;margin-bottom: 1.0725rem\"\n          >\n            <iframe src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/mfetPCwLLdU\" frameborder=\"0\" allow=\"accelerometer; autoplay; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture\" allowfullscreen style=\"\n            position: absolute;\n            top: 0;\n            left: 0;\n            width: 100%;\n            height: 100%;\n          \"></iframe>\n          </div>\n          \n<p>That doesn’t mean one must move into the countryside and become a monk or live like an Amish person, cutting themselves off from all modern technology. I love technology and the internet and would prefer to continue participating in it.</p>\n<p>I just don’t need 99.999% of the sh!t that people want me to buy. I don’t need a penthouse suite in a big city, a fancy car, expensive clothes, and whatever other meaningless crap everyone is peddling.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 421px;\"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/e3259e8b14a25ebf33bb67735146898b/da994/monster_eating_garbage.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 106.88836104513064%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;box-shadow:inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\"\n        alt=\"monster eating garbage\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/e3259e8b14a25ebf33bb67735146898b/da994/monster_eating_garbage.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/e3259e8b14a25ebf33bb67735146898b/8ee9c/monster_eating_garbage.jpg 148w,\n/static/e3259e8b14a25ebf33bb67735146898b/ebbe7/monster_eating_garbage.jpg 295w,\n/static/e3259e8b14a25ebf33bb67735146898b/da994/monster_eating_garbage.jpg 421w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 421px) 100vw, 421px\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>Give me a laptop and an internet connection and I’m good. I can access any book, article, video, TV show, song, or software ever made for free.</p>\n<p>When traveling, I used to stay at AirBnBs and hotels, but now I live in hostels because I prefer the social atmosphere. If I really wanted to save money and be free I could just sleep in a tent.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 400px;\"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/127cd8de39ab4b8dee66957cd9ef70a6/c7805/monster_eating_money.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 76.75%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;box-shadow:inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\"\n        alt=\"monster eating money\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/127cd8de39ab4b8dee66957cd9ef70a6/c7805/monster_eating_money.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/127cd8de39ab4b8dee66957cd9ef70a6/cf440/monster_eating_money.png 148w,\n/static/127cd8de39ab4b8dee66957cd9ef70a6/d2d38/monster_eating_money.png 295w,\n/static/127cd8de39ab4b8dee66957cd9ef70a6/c7805/monster_eating_money.png 400w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>The capitalist machine wants you to buy sh!t you don’t need with money you don’t have, because without your money it dies.</p>\n<p>Stop feeding the beast and let it die.</p>","frontmatter":{"title":"Simple Living (Stop Feeding the Beast)","date":"December 02, 2018"}}},"pageContext":{"isCreatedByStatefulCreatePages":false,"slug":"/simple-living/","previous":{"fields":{"slug":"/wealth-concentration/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Capitalism Naturally Trends Towards Increasing Wealth Concentration","tags":["politics","economics","philosophy"]}},"next":{"fields":{"slug":"/objectives-freedom-technology/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"The Objectives Society Should Strive For - Freedom and Technological Advancement","tags":["politics"]}}}}}